      "risk": "Synchronous standby failure causes primary to block all writes (cascading failure)",
      "severity": "high",
      "mitigation": "Configure synchronous_standby_names with multiple standbys (ANY 1 of standby1, standby2) so losing one standby doesn't block the primary. Patroni handles this configuration. Alert on replication lag and standby health."
    },
    {
      "risk": "In-process geo cache becomes stale, causing the Assignment Service to repeatedly shortlist unavailable couriers, increasing DB lock contention",
      "severity": "medium",
      "mitigation": "LISTEN/NOTIFY provides near-real-time invalidation. The SKIP LOCKED pattern gracefully handles stale candidates — they're simply skipped. Add a fallback: if all shortlisted candidates are locked, expand to a full DB geo-query as a slower but correct fallback path."
